# TRMNL Design System

When generating templaes for a plugin 
- use the styles as per the example in [description.example.html](mdc:design-system/description.example.html) [label.example.html](mdc:design-system/label.example.html) [table.example.html](mdc:design-system/table.example.html) [title-bar.example.html](mdc:design-system/title-bar.example.html) [title.example.html](mdc:design-system/title.example.html) [title-bar.example.html](mdc:design-system/title-bar.example.html) [clamp.example.html](mdc:design-system/clamp.example.html)

- do not include the header tags in a plugin, just include any styles in the body however just use those in [styles.css](mdc:design-system/styles.css) where possible based on the above examples

- secrets should not go into the plugin.json file. add these to the .env as additional_query_string_params

